reviews.text: Good and service were great!  I had their lunch special which was the small pizza and salad.  They served their delicious breadsticks at the beginning.  Everything was yummy.  My server Willow was awesome!  Should‚Äôve tried them sooner!

The pizza itself is pretty mediocre overall. Both the regular and thin crusts seem pre-made, which takes away from the freshness you'd hope for. Interestingly, the pizza actually tastes better when reheated in the oven the next day ‚Äî the flavors come out more and the texture improves. One issue I noticed was the inconsistent topping distribution ‚Äî some slices were loaded while others felt sparse. Not the worst pizza in town, but definitely room for improvement.

Many of our friends have told us to try Gondolier Pizza. We gave it a try last night and we were highly impressed. The place is very clean and the employees are nice and helpful. The house salad is large and delicious. We had a specialty pizza that was very, very good. Our waitress, Aubrey, did an excellent job of serving us. We did not try the desserts, but boy. oh boy, do the cakes look fantastic! We will definitely be returning.

I just ordered the house special, which was great, and the toppings were cooked perfectly! The breadsticks were terrific! I had chocolate cheesecake for dessert, which was a great way to end the evening! The service was excellent, and the atmosphere was very nice! I enjoyed it and definitely will be back! Highly recommended. A + 105

The food was very good, my waitress was extremely rude, I asked her for a to go box and she ignored me, I offered Her a 33 percent tip, and She just gave Me my money back, I will never eat here again; also She was only rude to Me after I spoke to the very friendly Aribic family if 4 next to Me, again don't come here, the waitress Emily is an awful person, the male waiter finally had to bring Me my dessert, I was at table 151 at 7:30 pm, the date of 5/13/25, aw You can see in the picture on My receipt, She (Emily S) refused My tip

detailedReviews.author: Cynthia Carey
detailedReviews.text: 1st things 1st our Waitress was real sweet & attentive!! No problems with her at all...         So that being said the cooks need to pay better attention to the orders & request from the customers.. our granddaughter ordered a medium pizza " light cheese" it came out loaded with cheese.. Sent it back to redo it.. It came back out & the waitress asked if it was ok? Granddaughter said yeah but it looked like the same pizza the edges were burnt & so was some of the toppings.. I believed it was the same pizza.. Very disappointed.. By the time it came out Husband & I were done eating..  Now I ordered cheese raviolis with light marinara and cheese on the top.. It was drenched!! So I just scraped it off went ahead & ate it.. I should have just ordered it with some sauce on the side.. I'll do that next time!!! Husband dinner was ok,, he didn't say anything so I assume he was good with it..   I wish these cooks would pay better attention to the orders.. I order things a certain way for a reason & I shouldn't have to explain why,, it should just get done right like I ask!!   It certainly isn't the waitress fault, she wrote it down & read it back so it's the cooks fixing the foods that are to blame!!

detailedReviews.author: Patty Hinton
detailedReviews.text: I really enjoy the food at Gondolier. One of my favorite meals is the gyros. I've had several different dishes, and I've never been disappointed. detailedReviews.author: Season W
detailedReviews.text:
Haven't been in a very long time, I was reminded why again.

1st off the good- Chocolate covered Cannoli and White Chocolate Raspberry cake were delicious. Server was nice

The bad- we got a sampler appetizer with the ravioli, zucchini, pickles and tenders, all fried. But when they came out it looked like a bland plate where all the food came pre frozen and battered, it was overcooked and bland, the zucchini was the only one that tasted any good.  Also got a grilled Chicken sandwich and salad, the sandwich was dry and chewy (overcooked) the salad was ok but it's only Iceberg lettuce and a few toppings, pretty basic

The ugly - walking in there is peeling tint on the windows and it has a distinct dated feel, there is also plexiglass still between all the booths, up for a while now as it's no longer very clear and you can tell it's been diminished overtime.

Overall, I won't go back anytime soon unless it's for a chocolate dipped Cannoli.
